<main id="main">
  <h1 id="title"> Theodore Roosevelt Jr. </h1>
    <p> The Rough Rider who became President </p> 
 <figure id="img-div">  <img class="smaller-image" id="image" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Theodore_Rooseveltnewtry.jpg/800px-Theodore_Rooseveltnewtry.jpg"/>
   <figcaption id="img-caption"> Colonel Theodore Roosevelt of the Rough Riders </figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section id="tribute-info">
    <u><h3> Important Moments of Theodore Roosevelt Jr.'s life:</h3></u>
  <ul>
        <li> <b>1858</b> - Born in Manhattan, New York</li>
        <li> <b>1864</b> - Witnessed Abraham Lincoln's funeral procession in Union Square, New York City</li>
        <li> <b>1865</b> - At age 7 opened "Roosevelt Museum of Natural Histroy" and filled with taxidermied animals that he caught or killed</li>
        <li> <b>1880</b> - Graduated Magna Cum Laude from Harvard</li>
        <li> <b>1898</b> - Formed First UR Volunteer Cavalry Regiment
        <li> <b>1898</b> - Returns from war in Cuba to become Governor of New York</li>
        <li> <b>1901</b> - Took office in March as Vice President under McKinley</li>
        <li> <b>1901</b> - Roosevelt becomes President as McKinley dies on September 14th from complications involing his gunshot wound from an assassination attempt</li>
        <li> <b>1906</b> - Passes the Antiquities Act which proclaimed 18 US monuments, 51 bird reserves, 4 game preserves, and 150 national forests
    <li> <b> 1919</b> - Dies at the age of 60</li>
    </ul>
          <em><p>"Death had to take Roosevelt sleeping, for if he had been awake, there would have been a fight."
            - Thomas R. Marshall</p></em>
 
        <h3 id="reference">Learn more about the Rough Rider at his <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theodore_Roosevelt" target="_blank" > Wikipedia entry</a></h3></section>
        
        
      
      
  
